= May Day, 1928

This year's May Day in Warsaw has seen violent clashes between the **Polish Socialist Party (PPS)** and the **Communist Party of Poland (KPP)**. The two factions, though both claiming to represent the working class, were never able to put aside their ideological differences.

The PPS, fiercely patriotic and determined to build a socialist Poland independent of Soviet influence, faced off against the KPP, who openly align themselves with Moscow and seek the overthrow of the Polish government in favor of a Soviet-style state. As both groups organized their own demonstrations, tensions quickly escalated, resulting in violent confrontations on the streets.

The police intervened to restore order, but the damage is done. The leftist movement remains deeply fractured, leaving us with a clear path to continue governing without strong opposition from the left.

